# MyMSD Training Env - Oct 2025 Mock/PoC Notes

\-Draft-

## Introduction

This design captures and replays HTTP traffic between Playwright-driven MyMSD scenarios and Datapower, and provides a simple mock API layer for Training environment. It ensures traffic relevance, storage management, reproducibility, and compliance. Protection of sensitive information with masking and validation.

## Goals and Objectives

- Execution of MyMSD business flows via Playwright in Dev/Test Environment
- Intercept and record only MyMSDâ†”Datapower traffic
- Store, refresh, and version recordings
- Expose a Spring Boot mock API backed by WireMock for training
- Enforce data quality through filters and validation
- Enable snapshotting, archiving, and version control of recordings
- Provide audit logging, masking, retention, and authorization workflows

## High-Level Architecture

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Key Design Decisions:

- Use WireMock standalone as a transparent HTTP proxy to minimize integration overhead
- Leverage WireMock Admin API for snapshot export/import to automate versioning
- Store recordings in a Git repository or Nexus to enable rollbacks and branching
- Implement Spring Boot wrapper to bootstrap WireMock stubs and manage lifecycle
- Add custom Java filters to WireMock for payload validation and masking as required

## Component Breakdown

| **Component** | **Description** | **Technology** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Automated Traffic Generation | Executes MyMSD scenarios; routes all HTTP through WireMock proxy | Playwright |
| Network Traffic Capture | Captures and filters requests/responses between Playwright and Datapower | WireMock |
| Translation and Storage | Persists recordings; refreshes on new test runs | WireMock + File System |
| Mock API Integration | Hosts recorded mappings; matches inbound calls to stubbed responses | Spring Boot + WireMock |
| Data Quality | Validates and sanitizes payloads; ensures only relevant traffic is stored | WireMock Extensions |
| Archiving & Reproducibility | Exports snapshots; stores in Git or Nexus; versions the recordings | WireMock Admin API; Git |
| CI/CD | Create pipeline to run playwright, record using WireMock and store snapshots | Jenkins |

## Data Flow

- Playwright launches MyMSD test suite with HTTP proxy pointing at WireMock.
- WireMock intercepts each request; applies filters to allow only MyMSDâ†”Datapower traffic.
- Filter-passed traffic is recorded as request/response pairs.
- Recording files are written to a versioned directory.
- Upon completion, WireMock Admin API is invoked to snapshot the recordings.
- Snapshot archives are committed to Git or pushed to Nexus.
- Spring Boot mock server reads selected snapshot; serves stubbed responses for Training environment.

## Deployment and Environment Setup

- Setup Jenkins pipelines to execute playwright and snapshot WireMock recordings.
- Provision WireMock docker image and configure network for Dev/Test environment deployment.
- Deploy Spring Boot mock server on training environment.
- Configure secure credentials for Git/Nexus pushes.
- Define environment variables for proxy host/port.
- Schedule snapshot and Git commit jobs with every MyMSD release.
